Vheadline
p2
VFeast of melody
p3
sVnews
p4
VLight music artistes, Suhasini Anand and Usha Prasad organised &#8216;Ek Haseen Shaam &#8211; Asha Ke Naam', an evening of Asha Bhonsle's songs from Hindi feature films. Both of them individually, together and along with David, Ramanarayan and Jayalakshmi regaled the audience at Kalabharathi singing for over two hours.Solos like, Shoukh nazar ki bijliyan from Woh Kaun Thee by Usha, duets Kajra Mohabattwala from Kismat and the likes by her along with David stood out. Rendering solos like Koun Aya from Waqt, Jaayiye Aap Kaha from Mere Sanam besides duets like Bohot shukriya from Ek Musafir Ek Haseena along with her father-guru Palagummi Rajagopal and Ramnarayan, Suhasini regaled everyone in the auditorium. Jhoomka gira-re from Mera Saya by Jayalakshmi was equally enchanting. Bheeshma's orchestra with Sai and Ramana on keyboards, melodious flute by Kurmanatham, pads by young Pavankumar, tabla by Ramanamurthy and Paydi Raju, drums by E. Ramanish and Simhachalm, guitar by Bheeshma and rhythms by V. Seetaramaih was excellent.Dr. Ramnarayan compered the programme. Guests of honour S. Vijayakumarand A. Prasanna Kumar felicitated veterans Palagummi Rajagopal and V. Seetharamaiah on the occasion. Prime disciple of music director Salur Rajeswara Rao, Rajagopal did music for about a dozen Telugu feature films and also sang some songs besides composing and producing albums of private songs like Bhakthi Gana Sudha and so on. Seetha Ramaiah is a well known exponent of both Hindustani and Carnatik styles of music.
